Subject: [PATCH] Fix login branding bug, split demo mode, mobile fixes, brand
 prominence, and finish doc cleanup

- Session/login: added explicitSociety flag so /login no longer shows
  Rajhans Tower's branding to every visitor by default. Only shows a
  specific society once one was chosen on purpose (share link, resolved
  membership, demo pick).
- Split demo mode onto its own /demo page, out of /login entirely.
- Fixed mobile: no way to reach /login from a phone (button was hidden
  below sm breakpoint, mobile menu never got a login link). Public
  header/footer now show the full wordmark at every size, not just a
  bare symbol on mobile.
- Public site now defaults to Gujarati, English is the toggle.
- Prangan One branding now visible (with the name, not just the mark)
  on resident, admin, and accountant screens, per explicit instruction.
  Fixed a real contrast bug found in the process: the admin/accountant
  sidebar's Powered By line used the navy mark on a navy background.
- Fixed FAQ's premature 'isolated at the database level' claim, removed
  Contact's broken wa.me link with no number, softened Pricing's
  WhatsApp wording and added concrete per-flat-count examples.
- Added light grouping to the admin sidebar nav (Overview/Money/
  Operations/Communication/Settings), same items, same routes.
- Finished the documentation cleanup: README (owner console framing,
  payment-flow description, active-vs-deferred ordering, removed the
  closing Essancia line), DESIGN_SYSTEM.md's stale /saas/* references,
  robots.txt's unnecessary /home allow, .env.example's Razorpay/
  WhatsApp placeholders, and two currently-actionable stale file paths
  inside CLAUDE_CODE_NEXT_STEPS.md's own ready-to-paste prompts.
  Historical session-log entries left alone on purpose, with a note
  explaining why.
