+## Session 6 summary (this session): login architecture fix, demo/login split, mobile fixes, and the rest of the documentation cleanup
+
+Another external review (this time checking the actual live site plus real device screenshots, not just the code) caught two genuinely important things the previous sessions missed, both confirmed by reading the real code before touching anything, not just trusted on faith.
+
+- **Fixed the real bug: `/login` was showing Rajhans Tower's branding to every visitor.** Root cause: every fresh session defaults to `societyId: soc_rajhans` (reasonable, other pages need *some* active society to render against), and Login.tsx blindly rendered whatever society was active. Fix: `Session` gained an `explicitSociety: boolean` flag, true only when a society was chosen on purpose (a `/s/:slug` share link, a resolved membership, a demo flat pick), false for a session just sitting on the raw default. Login.tsx now shows Prangan One's own generic branding unless that flag is true. Didn't touch the default society resolution itself, that stays as-is since too much else depends on it.
+- **Split demo mode onto its own `/demo` page, out of `/login` entirely.** The real login screen now only ever has the honest email flow, never a "become the owner" button, regardless of `VITE_DEMO_MODE`. `/demo` has its own gate (the same flag) and its own honest "not available" state when it's off.
+- **Fixed a real mobile bug: there was no way to reach `/login` from a phone.** The desktop "Log in" button was `hidden` below the `sm` breakpoint, and the mobile hamburger menu never got a login link added when it was built. Confirmed by reading the actual JSX, not just the screenshot. Fixed: the mobile menu now leads with a prominent login button.
+- **Public header/footer show the full wordmark at every size now, including mobile.** Previously mobile showed the bare symbol with no name at all, which defeats the point of brand recognition on the exact surface most people will meet it on first.
+- **Public site now defaults to Gujarati, English is the toggle-in option.** This reverses the original roadmap's English-default assumption, on the person's explicit instruction, since real visitors are finding this through WhatsApp shares and word of mouth in Gujarati. `index.html`'s static fallback (what shows before any JS runs) was updated to match.
+- **Prangan One branding is now genuinely visible on resident, admin, and accountant screens, with the name, not just the mark**, on the explicit instruction that this is a deliberate brand-recognition decision, not an oversight: a thin "Powered by [wordmark]" strip above the resident header, a properly-sized (and finally *visible*, see below) lockup at the bottom of the admin/accountant sidebar, and a small mark in the admin/accountant mobile header. Society identity stays primary in all three, this is a visible secondary signature, not equal billing.
+- **Fixed a real contrast bug found while doing the above**: the admin/accountant sidebar's old "Powered by Prangan One" line used the navy-colored mark on a navy-900 background, nearly invisible. `PoweredByPrangan` now takes a `dark` prop and shows the real wordmark image (not just the symbol plus repeated text), so the name stays legible on both light and dark surfaces.
+- **Fixed the FAQ's premature claim** ("isolated at the database level") to honestly describe the current state (browser-local, no shared backend yet) and what's coming, instead of a claim that wasn't true yet.
+- **Removed the Contact page's broken WhatsApp button** (linked to bare `wa.me` with no number), softened the copy to only mention email until a real number exists. One-line comment marks exactly where to add it back.
+- **Pricing page**: softened "WhatsApp reminders" to "one-tap WhatsApp reminder sharing" (matches what actually exists, share links, not automation), and added two concrete examples (24 flats = ₹240/month, 100 flats = ₹1,000/month) addressing the "looks unfinished, too much empty space" feedback with actual content instead of decoration.
+- **Finished the documentation cleanup flagged as unsorted last session**: README's owner-console description, payment-flow description (was calling the real manual+pending-confirmation flow a "placeholder", it isn't one), and Next-steps ordering (Supabase work is now clearly "active", Razorpay/WhatsApp API clearly "deferred") are all fixed. Removed the closing Essancia attribution line, no legal requirement for it and it doesn't fit a standalone product identity. `docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`'s stale `/saas/*` references fixed. `robots.txt`'s unnecessary `/home` allow removed (it only redirects) and `/demo` added to the disallow list. `.env.example`'s Razorpay/WhatsApp placeholders removed entirely, replaced with a plain explanatory comment, no vendor names. Found and fixed two *currently-actionable* stale file paths inside `CLAUDE_CODE_NEXT_STEPS.md`'s own ready-to-paste prompts (they still said `src/pages/saas/...`, which would have sent a future session to a path that doesn't exist), left the historical session-log entries alone, added one line at the top noting explicitly why those are historical, not current, so nobody mistakes one for the other later.
+
+**What this pass deliberately did not touch**: no redesign, no new dependencies, no Supabase work, no change to the working resident/admin/accountant product screens beyond the branding additions explicitly requested, no change to the official brand asset files themselves.
+
